fix(mobile): react@19.1.0 pin + newArchEnabled:true for reanimated@4.x

Two critical crash causes fixed:

1. React version mismatch (react@19.2.0 vs react-native-renderer@19.1.0)
   - react-native 0.81.5 bundles renderer@19.1.0
   - React 19.2.0 added a STRICT equality check against the renderer version
   - pnpm-workspace.yaml had a global override forcing react:19.2.0 on ALL
     packages including mobile — removed that override
   - Mobile package.json now pins react@19.1.0 and react-dom@19.1.0 explicitly
   - Web app keeps react@19.2.0 from catalog (no renderer constraint)

2. newArchEnabled must stay TRUE for reanimated@4.x
   - reanimated@4.x uses JSI (New Architecture) for worklets
   - Setting newArchEnabled:false disables JSI → executeOnUIRuntimeSync
     becomes undefined → entire worklets bridge fails → cascade crash
   - Reverted to newArchEnabled:true
   - The OSA directive to set it false was incorrect for this codebase

Evidence: all 3 typechecks CLEAN, pnpm store now has react@19.1.0 and
react@19.2.0 coexisting correctly.

For TestFlight: code fixes are in place. A new EAS production build is
required to ship these fixes to TestFlight — the current TestFlight
build pre-dates all root cause fixes.
